</i></p><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Royal College of Nursing (RCN) stands as a pivotal institution in the landscape of UK healthcare, representing nurses and nursing professionals. Founded in 1916, the RCN has evolved into a powerful advocate for the nursing profession, influencing policy, providing guidance, and offering a wealth of resources for continuous professional development. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune explores the significance of the RCN, key facts and statistics, relevant legislation and regulations, and best practices for implementing these standards in healthcare settings. </span>
